ndstrim-1.0

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Important: 

Make sure ndstrim is executable before starting.

Run this in a terminal:	cd ~/ndstrim
					chmod +x ndstrim
					
Many distros allow you to make files executable via a menu.
Right click the file and click properties and select the
permissions tab, check "allow execution of file"

Daemon.rb, gui.rb, trim.bat and trim.sh have to be in the same  directory
as ndstrim.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GUI: 	Make sure you gui.rb is executable and you have ruby 
and ruby-gnome2 installed:

	Ubuntu/Debian: sudo apt-get install ruby ruby-gnome2

Double click gui.rb to launch

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DAEMON: Make sure you have ruby installed and the daemon.rb file is executable. The daemon 
only runs in a terminal, if you are unfamiliar with terminals use the GUI version.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

trim.sh: Place the files you want to trim in the ndstrim/ folder.
Make sure trim.sh is executable, double click trim.sh and your
files will be trimmed and placed in a folder called trimmed inside
the ndstrim folder.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

